# Production Terraform Best Practices

### Structure

```text
terraform/
├── modules/
├── environments/
│   ├── dev
│   ├── stage
│   └── prod
├── backend.tf
├── providers.tf
├── variables.tf
├── outputs.tf
```

### Security

* Store state remotely in S3.
* Enable state locking with DynamoDB.
* Never hardcode secrets.
* Use IAM roles.
* Encrypt S3 state buckets.
* Use separate AWS accounts for dev/stage/prod.

### Optimization

* Reusable modules
* Workspaces
* CI/CD integration with Jenkins
* Automated validation
* Automated security scanning

