# AWS Core Services Explained (English + Hinglish)

---

# 1. Amazon EC2 (Elastic Compute Cloud)

## English

EC2 provides virtual servers in the cloud. You can launch Linux or Windows servers, install applications, and scale as needed.

Common Tasks:

* Launch instances
* Create AMIs
* Configure Security Groups
* Monitor using CloudWatch

Example AWS CLI:

```bash
aws ec2 describe-instances
```

---

## Hinglish

EC2 AWS ka virtual server hai.

Aap:

* Linux server launch kar sakte ho
* Windows server launch kar sakte ho
* Applications host kar sakte ho
* Scale up/down kar sakte ho

Example:
Agar website host karni hai to EC2 instance create karte hain aur usme Nginx ya Apache install karte hain.

---

# 2. Amazon VPC (Virtual Private Cloud)

## English

VPC provides an isolated network inside AWS.

Components:

* VPC
* Subnets
* Route Tables
* Internet Gateway
* NAT Gateway
* Security Groups

Architecture:

```text
VPC
 |
 +-- Public Subnet
 |
 +-- Private Subnet
```

---

## Hinglish

VPC AWS ka private network hai.

Jaise company ke office ka network hota hai waise hi AWS me VPC hota hai.

Public Subnet:

* Internet access

Private Subnet:

* No direct internet access

---

# 3. Amazon S3

## English

S3 is object storage used for:

* Images
* Videos
* Backups
* Static websites

Features:

* Versioning
* Lifecycle Policies
* Encryption

Upload File:

```bash
aws s3 cp file.txt s3://mybucket
```

---

## Hinglish

S3 AWS ka storage service hai.

Store kar sakte hain:

* Images
* Videos
* Backups
* Logs

Example:
Website ke images S3 me rakh sakte hain.

---

# 4. Amazon EBS

## English

EBS provides block storage attached to EC2.

Features:

* SSD Volumes
* Snapshots
* Backup

Snapshot:

```bash
aws ec2 create-snapshot \
--volume-id vol-12345
```

---

## Hinglish

EBS EC2 server ki hard disk hai.

Agar server delete ho jaye to snapshot se recover kar sakte hain.

---

# 5. Amazon EFS

## English

Elastic File System is shared storage.

Multiple EC2 servers can access the same files.

Use Cases:

* Shared uploads
* Kubernetes storage
* CMS applications

---

## Hinglish

EFS ek shared network drive hai.

Multiple EC2 servers same files access kar sakte hain.

---

# 6. Load Balancer

## Application Load Balancer (ALB)

### English

Routes HTTP/HTTPS traffic.

```text
Users
  |
 ALB
  |
EC2 Instances
```

---

### Hinglish

ALB traffic ko multiple servers me distribute karta hai.

Agar ek server down ho jaye to request dusre server par jayegi.

---

## Network Load Balancer (NLB)

### English

Handles TCP/UDP traffic with very high performance.

### Hinglish

High-performance traffic ke liye use hota hai.

Gaming aur financial systems me common hai.

---

# 7. Auto Scaling

## English

Automatically adds/removes servers based on load.

Example:

```text
CPU > 80%
Add 2 EC2 Instances
```

---

## Hinglish

Traffic badhe to naye servers automatically create ho jate hain.

Traffic kam ho to servers delete ho jate hain.

---

# 8. Amazon RDS

## English

Managed database service.

Supports:

* MySQL
* PostgreSQL
* MariaDB
* SQL Server

Backup:

```text
Automatic Daily Backup
```

---

## Hinglish

AWS database manage karta hai.

Hume:

* Patch nahi lagana
* Backup manually nahi lena

